==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Telephone exchange
<hw>Tel`e*phone ex*change"</hw>. <def>A central office in which the
wires of telephones from local subscribers may be connected by switches
to other local telephones or to long-distance lines, to permit
transmission of conversation or data.</def> <note>In the late 1990's the
traditional copper wires connecting local telephones to the telephone
exchange have begun to be replaced with optical fiber
connections.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Telephonic</ent>⟦br⟧
